children.text: There are areas where the ceiling insulation has not been installed over the top plates, which will be reducing the effectiveness of the thermal performance.
The relevant Australian Standard AS 3900 Bulk Thermal Insulation states in section 5.3.4 Horizontal ceilings below pitched roofs that
‘Bulk insulation in ceilings shall extend not less than 50 mm beyond the inside face of the walls enclosing the space to be insulated’ .
The ceiling insulation must be extended to 50mm over the top plates to ensure thermal performance.
